# 🧪 IMC Pipeline - Step 1: Convert MCD to TIFF

This pipeline was inspired by [deep-imcyto](https://github.com/FrancisCrickInstitute/deep-imcyto).  
It uses Docker to convert MCD files to TIFF format.

---

## 📦 Requirements

Make sure you have [Docker](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop) installed and working on your system.

---

## 🚀 Step 1: Convert MCD Files to TIFF

### 🔹 1.1 Download Test Data

Download all the files and folders from the `test_folder` directory into your local project folder.  
Example:

```bash
/Volumes/your_name/MAC_1/Docker/IMC_pipeline/test_data
```

---

### 🔹 1.2 Place Your MCD Files

Place all your `.mcd` files into the `Raw` subfolder of your project directory:

```
/Your_Project/Raw
```

---

### 🔹 1.3 Edit `Sample_list.csv`

Open `Sample_list.csv` in your project folder and **replace all paths with `/mnt`**, since Docker will access files using `/mnt`.

> ✅ Example:
> Replace:
> `/Volumes/lyu.yang/MAC_1/Docker/IMC_pipeline/test_data/Raw/sample1.mcd`  
> With:
> `/mnt/Raw/sample1.mcd`

---

### 🔹 1.4 Configure the Script

Open the script `1_step1_MCD_tiff.sh` and edit the following line:

```bash
WORKING_DIR="/path/to/your/local/project"
```

Replace it with the **full path to your local project folder**.

---

### 🔹 1.5 Run the Pipeline

From your terminal, run:

```bash
bash 1_step1_MCD_tiff.sh
```

This will:
- Start a Docker container
- Mount your local folder into the container
- Convert MCD files in `/mnt/Raw` to TIFF format

---

## 📁 Example Directory Structure

```bash
IMC_pipeline/
├── 1_step1_MCD_tiff.sh
├── Sample_list.csv       # Edited with /mnt paths
├── Raw/                  # Contains your .mcd files
├── Tiff/                 # Output TIFFs go here
```

